President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his Administration. The nominations include Lynda Blanchard of Alabama to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Slovenia. Blanchard is a co-founder of the 100X Development Foundation and has worked in various regions around the world to improve the lives of children and eradicate poverty. 

Robert A. Destro of Virginia has been nominated to be the Assistant Secretary of State for Democracy, Human Rights, and Labor. Destro is a human rights advocate and civil rights attorney, with expertise in elections and employment law. He currently serves as a professor of law and director of the Institute for Policy Research and Catholic Studies at The Catholic University of America.

Rick A. Dearborn of Oklahoma has been nominated to be a Member of the Amtrak Board of Directors for a term of five years. Dearborn previously served as Deputy Chief of Staff for President Trump and as the Chief of Staff for Senator Jeff Sessions.

Mark Montgomery of Virginia has been nominated to be an Assistant Administrator of the United States Agency for International Development for the Bureau for Democracy, Conflict, and Humanitarian Assistance. Montgomery is currently the policy director for the Senate Armed Services Committee and retired as a Rear Admiral in the United States Navy.

Kimberly A. Reed of West Virginia has been nominated to be President of the Export-Import Bank for a term of four years. Reed previously served as president of the International Food Information Council Foundation and headed the Community Development Financial Institutions Fund at the United States Department of the Treasury.

These nominations are subject to Senate confirmation.